{"title":"UAE Tour Men 2024: Route, TV and everything you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uae-tour-men-preview","date":1708099888000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uae-tour-men-preview\">UAE Tour Men 2024: Route, TV and everything you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>After Lotte Kopecky (SD Worx-Protime) won the UAE Tour Women, all eyes turn to the men’s peloton as they kick off their week-long race from 19th-25th February 2024.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last year’s edition was won by <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel</a> (Soudal-QuickStep) ahead of Luke Plapp (Ineos Grenadiers) and Adam Yates (<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/uae-team-emirates\" target=\"_blank\">UAE Team Emirates)</a>. Evenepoel is in fine form having just won the Figueria Champions Classic by a 53km solo breakaway as Yates won the final stage and the overall classification at the Tour of Oman. Plapp, now at Jayco-AlUla, also kicked off the season with a strong start Down Under, securing a gold medal in both the Australian national road race and individual time-trial.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yates will return to the start line this year, eyeing overall victory and another summit finish atop Jebel Hafeet on the final day.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-log-lotte-kopecky-uae-tour\">Pro Log: Lotte Kopecky wins UAE Tour Women, Mads Pedersen dominates Tour de la Provence, Adrien Petit’s heart-warming act of respect and update on Taco van der Hoorn’s concussion</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\">How to watch cycling post-GCN+</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/saudi-pro-cycling-league\">What is the rumoured Saudi racing league – and what would it mean for pro cycling?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"668\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj-970x668.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj-970x668.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj-300x207.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj-768x529.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj-1536x1058.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj-750x516.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj-1140x785.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Fp5XTbkWYAEc7Uj.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>UAE Tour</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Date:</strong> 19th-25th February 2024<br /><strong>Start</strong>: Al Dhafra<br /><strong>Finish:</strong> Jebel Hafeet<br /><strong>Stages:</strong> 7<br /><strong>Distance:</strong> 985.1km<br /><strong>2023 winner:</strong> Remco Evenepoel (Soudal-QuickStep)<br /><strong>UK television coverage:</strong> Discovery+, Eurosport, Eurosport 2 </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour 2024: The route</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As usual, the UAE Tour is a flat affair for the sprinters minus the two summit finishes of Jebel Jais on Stage 3 and Jebel Hafeet on Stage 7, where the GC will be decided.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1, Monday 19th February: Al Dhafra – Liwa, 143km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"478\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.05.10-970x478.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.05.10-970x478.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.05.10-300x148.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.05.10-768x379.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.05.10-750x370.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.05.10-1140x562.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.05.10.png 1274w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The first stage of the men’s UAE Tour is a flat 143km ride from Al Dhafra to Liwa. Last year’s opener, which also began in Al Dhafra, was won by Tim Merlier (Soudal-QuickStep).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2, Tuesday 20th February: Al Hudayriat – Al Hudayriat, 12.1km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"483\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12-970x483.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12-970x483.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12-300x150.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12-768x383.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12-360x180.png 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12-750x374.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12-1140x568.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.08.12.png 1276w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 2 is a 12.1km race against the clock in an individual time-trial around Al Hudayriyat Island.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3, Wednesday 21st February: Al Marjan – Jebel Jais, 176km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"483\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03-970x483.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03-970x483.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03-300x149.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03-768x382.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03-360x180.png 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03-750x373.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03-1140x567.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.10.03.png 1278w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fasten your seatbelts, it’s the first summit finish of the UAE Tour at Jebel Jais. Last year, Movistar’s Albert Torres and Einer Rubio broke away in the final 11km of the stage, Torres pulling off as Rubio went on solo, winning the stage on his birthday ahead of Evenepoel and Yates. Rubio will be back again this year, can he repeat the feat?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4, Thursday 22nd February: Dubai – Dubai, 173km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"481\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12-970x481.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12-970x481.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12-300x149.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12-768x381.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12-360x180.png 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12-750x372.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12-1140x566.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.22.12.png 1278w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Back to level roads now for a 172.7km trip from Dubai to Dubai Harbour. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5, Friday 23rd February: Al Aqah – Umm al Quwain, 182km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.23.45-970x479.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.23.45-970x479.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.23.45-300x148.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.23.45-768x379.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.23.45-750x370.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.23.45-1140x563.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.23.45.png 1272w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 5 has a slight bump in the road but for the most part is another flat day. Dylan Groenewegen (Jayco-AlUla) won the 170km stage towards Umm al Quwain in 2023.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6, Saturday 24th February: Abu Dhabi – Abu Dhabi, 138km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10-970x482.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10-970x482.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10-300x149.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10-768x382.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10-360x180.png 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10-750x373.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10-1140x566.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.30.10.png 1264w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I could frantically search the thesaurus for another word similar to flat, but that’s exactly what this is. Flat.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 7, Sunday 25th February: Al Ain – Jebel Hafeet, 161km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.37.24-970x480.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.37.24-970x480.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.37.24-300x148.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.37.24-768x380.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.37.24-750x371.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.37.24-1140x564.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-16-at-12.37.24.png 1278w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The final day of the UAE Tour goes up in elevation for the classic finish atop Jebel Hafeet (10.8km, 7%). Yates claimed stage honours here in 2023 as Evenepoel won overall. Will Yates reach the top step of the GC podium in 2024?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour 2024: How to watch</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re still mourning the loss of GCN+, but the UAE Tour 2024 will be available to watch in the UK on <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> for £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. It will also be shown on the TV channel Eurosport 2 in the UK.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 1, Monday 19th February</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:45 – 12:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 2: Tuesday 20th February</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:45 – 12:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 3, Wednesday 21st February</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:45 – 12:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 4, Thursday 22nd February</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:45 – 12:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 5, Friday 23rd February</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 10:45 – 12:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 6, Saturday 24th February</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:45 – 12:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 7, Sunday 25th February</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:45 – 12:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour 2024: Start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=9800&amp;y=2024&amp;k=8\" target=\"_blank\">FirstCycling.com</a></em></p></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uae-tour-men-preview\">UAE Tour Men 2024: Route, TV and everything you need to know</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"857e99ead584c694e4736fead6718b057176ad6d1f498f1f0701b3110eb3f353","category":"Cycling"}